Here's a modified version of the program that takes one argument from the command line and prints whether that value is positive, negative, or zero in C++:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <cstdlib>

void checkNumber(int num) {
    if (num > 0) {
        std::cout << "Positive" << std::endl;
    } else if (num < 0) {
        std::cout << "Negative" << std::endl;
    } else {
